A barber, Bala Mohammed, 24,  has been arraigned at an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly attacking two brothers with an iron rod during a disagreement. Mohammed pleaded not guilty to the charge of unlawful infliction of grievous harm, breach of the peace and assault. Prosecuting Sergeant Ishola Samuel said the defendant used the iron rod to injure the brothers  during a feud over unpaid electricity bills. He alleged that the defendant used the rod to inflict a deep cut and serious injuries on George Francis’ stomach. Samuel alleged that the defendant also used the iron rod to injure Sunday Francis, the complainant’s brother, on his lower jaw. The prosecutor said the defendant committed the offence on January 27. Magistrate A.I. Abina granted the defendant  N300, 000 bail, with two sureties in the like sum. She adjourned till April 24.